    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1972-07-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1972-07-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="170"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d170">
                <head>170. National Security Decision Memorandum 173<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d170fn1">Source: National Archives, <persName corresp="#p_NRM1"
                            >Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                            >NSC</gloss> Files, Box 699, Country Files—Europe, Poland, Vol. II 1972.
                        Confidential. Copies were also sent to the Secretary of Agriculture, the
                        Presidentʼs Special Representative for Trade Negotiations, and the President
                        of the Export-Import Bank. Also issued as <gloss target="#t_CIEPDM1"
                            >CIEPDM</gloss> 8.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1972-07-07">July 7, 1972</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="to">
                    <head>TO</head>
                    <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of the Treasury</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of Commerce</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Polish-<gloss target="#t_US1">US</gloss> Economic Relations</item>
                </list>
                <pb facs="0452" n="408" xml:id="pg_408"/>
                <list>
                    <label>
                        <hi rend="italic">1.</hi>
                    </label>
                    <item>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="italic">Export-Import Bank Credit Facilities</hi>
                        </p>
                        <p>Exercise of the Presidentʼs authority to extend these facilities is tied
                            to a solution of the claims of <gloss target="#t_US1">US</gloss> holders
                            of dollar bonds issued by the pre-war Polish government. The Secretary
                            of State should notify the Foreign Bondholders Council that the <gloss
                                target="#t_US1">US</gloss> Government continues to favor a
                            reasonable settlement of <gloss target="#t_US1">US</gloss> holdersʼ
                            claims within a reasonable time. If Polish government representatives
                            inquire when Export-Import Bank credit facilities can be made available
                            to Poland, they should be informed that the President, in accordance
                            with his discussions in Warsaw, will make this decision in light of the
                            status of negotiations between the Polish government and the
                            bondholdersʼ representatives.</p>
                    </item>
                    <label>
                        <hi rend="italic">2.</hi>
                    </label>
                    <item>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="italic">Deferral of <gloss target="#t_PL4801">PL–480</gloss>
                                Dollar Debt</hi>
                        </p>
                        <p>In response to Chairman <persName corresp="#p_JP1"
                            >Jaroszewicz</persName>ʼs message on this subject to the President of
                            June 5, 1972,<note n="2" xml:id="d170fn2">See <ref target="#d169"
                                    >Document 169</ref> and <ref target="#d169fn2">footnote 2
                                    thereto</ref>. An unofficial translation of <persName
                                    corresp="#p_JP1">Jaroszewicz</persName>ʼs letter of June 5 is
                                also attached to a June 16 memorandum from <persName
                                    corresp="#p_DDEJ1">David</persName> to <persName
                                    corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName>. (National Archives,
                                    <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> Presidential
                                Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, Box 699,
                                Country Files—Europe, Poland, Vol. II 1972)</note> the Department of
                            State, after appropriate coordination with the Department of Commerce
                            and other agencies, should inform the Polish government that we are
                            willing to defer the dollar tranches under the <gloss target="#t_PL4801"
                                >PL–480</gloss> agreements which fall due in the years 1973–1974 for
                            a period of five years, i.e., so that these payments will be made in the
                            years 1977 and 1978. Toward the end of 1974 we would be prepared to
                            consider deferral of further tranches. This is contingent, however, upon
                            appropriate assurances from the Polish government, as proposed in the
                            aide-mémoire of December 2, 1971,<note n="3" xml:id="d170fn3">Not
                                found.</note> and Chairman <persName corresp="#p_JP1"
                                >Jaroszewicz</persName>ʼs letter of June 5, 1972, to the President,
                            that Polish enterprises will purchase in the United States during the
                            period 1972–1973 machinery and equipment for the amount equivalent to
                            the total of deferred tranches.</p>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>
                                <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">
                                    <hi rend="strong">Henry A. Kissinger</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <persName corresp="#p_FPM1">
                                    <hi rend="strong">PMF</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
